reviewText: If you liked "Dilbert", the previous release of the show was superior to this one on pretty much every front.

I bought this DVD recently at a big box store for just $5.  Mill Creek has recently put out this new DVD set for Dilbert  (they also put out a Married with Children set) and they are able to keep the prices low because there are no extras to speak of.  All the episodes are complete and present, there is just no special features.  But at just $5 for the complete series of one of the best shows ever, you can't beat that!

Mill Creek botches another release. Surprise, surprise.

Dilbert is one of the funniest and most underrated TV series of the past 20 years.

In 2004, Sony put out a Complete Series set loaded to the gills with special features. That release is unfortunately now out of print, however, it can be had for very cheap.

This re-issue Mill Creek has put out condenses the series down from 4 to 3 discs (resulting in higher artifacting and compression) along with stripping all of the bonus features.

Yeah, it's cheap, but you get what you pay for.

Seek out the original release if you want to enjoy this show the way it was meant to be.

Dilbert is one of my all-time favourite series. My only regret is that it was not aired for more seasons.

Physical product: 4/5 stars.  The production value for the price is great.  The discs contain nothing but the episodes, so if you don't care about bonuses, this is the cheaper choice.  I take away a star for two reasons, one minor and one major.  Minor: the discs are stacked on top of each other in the case, making it more challenging to pick your disc and increasing the chance of scratches.  Major: the episodes are out of order!  It doesn't matter too much in later episodes, since they are mostly just one-off stories, but near the beginning in which there is a serial story, it can lead to confusion.

Content: 0/5 stars.  This show is incredibly unfunny.  The jokes frequently are poorly delivered with bad timing and no humor.  It's like a stand-up comedian whose material isn't that good, and after delivering a flat joke, mugs on the stage, saying, "Eh?  Eh?"

Average score: 2/5

I ordered this as it was recommended to me through amazon. I remember being in high school was on and catching one show. The set is bare bones and very cost friendly. I would highly recommend this set for anyone who enjoys cartoons for older audiences. It has great writing and some very loveable characters. For $6, it's a very sweet deal. Picture quality is sharp and the colors really pop.

If you like the Dilbert Comics or just love to hate work, this is the series for you. Unfortunately, it was short lived, but I strongly think the Dilbert series is a hidden gem. The series is well written, funny, and insightful. You'll find yourself laughing, but also relating to the characters well. When you can understand and empathize with characters, it is so much more powerful and enjoyable
